715
00:41:27.884 --> 00:41:30.764
And in the fallopian tube, a lesion develops called STICS.

716
00:41:31.544 --> 00:41:35.474
And if you look in studies that estimate the incidence of STICS in the

717
00:41:35.504 --> 00:41:36.684
healthy population, some

718
00:41:37.864 --> 00:41:41.644
studies will tell you one in 1,000 healthy women has STIC

719
00:41:41.684 --> 00:41:45.404
lesions. And the next study tells you one in 50 women has these lesions.

720
00:41:45.424 --> 00:41:47.914
And it changes wildly based on the study that you look at.

721
00:41:49.004 --> 00:41:52.804
So in this application, we took a whole fallopian tube and exhaustively sectioned

