00:44:37.332 --> 00:44:41.152
challenging. Say if you see something amazing within this block of tissue and you

768
00:44:41.162 --> 00:44:45.082
want to go back and apply something new to it, like xenium, you would have

769
00:44:45.092 --> 00:44:48.392
to take that block, go back and cut it in the clinic, and hope that you can

770
00:44:48.432 --> 00:44:50.612
identify the slide that had the entity you wanted to see.

771
00:44:52.252 --> 00:44:55.552
On the second hand, we have sectioning-based technologies that you could take the

772
00:44:55.592 --> 00:44:59.352
same block of tissue, section it the same way as done in conventional 2D

