00:44:59.372 --> 00:45:03.192
pathology, and then apply a sequence of techniques to each of those

774
00:45:03.232 --> 00:45:03.732
sections.

775
00:45:04.732 --> 00:45:08.692
Advantages include that you can quite easily apply multi-omics to this.

776
00:45:08.752 --> 00:45:12.532
You can do cyclic IF, H&amp;E, conventional staining

777
00:45:12.552 --> 00:45:16.002
techniques, as well as today's advanced and expensive multi-omics.

778
00:45:16.712 --> 00:45:17.102
While

779
00:45:17.932 --> 00:45:21.612
some of the disadvantages can be that the act of cutting the tissue

780
00:45:22.532 --> 00:45:23.972
can exhaust clinical blocks.

781
00:45:25.852 --> 00:45:29.792
Also, that the sectioning is quite challenging and time-consuming, but at the

782
00:45:29.852 --> 00:45:33.452
end, it's one of the only ways to effectively multiplex that we have today.

783
00:45:35.412 --> 00:45:39.112
Okay, so if we think of the tissue atlas community, a lot of us think of it as

784
00:45:39.121 --> 00:45:40.732
something that just developed.

